<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-11-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-11-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="1686" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1686">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No 419.11 D 29/32.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">American Chargé
                                    d’Affaires</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-11-23">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 23, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In reply to your No. 240, of the 1st
                            instant, I desire to say that the Department is glad to learn of the
                            apparently sincere determination of the present administration of Panama
                            to identify and punish those responsible for the killing and wounding of
                            American citizens in Panama on July 4 last, and trusts that the
                            investigation which has been undertaken will lead to prompt results
                            along this line.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>